    <description>http://www.computerandvideogames.com/article.php?id=210507
[center][img]http://medialib.computerandvideogames.com/screens/screenshot_212539_thumb300.jpg[/img][/center]

&lt;blockquote&gt;The Sega Mega Dive is set to return to the shops, courtesy of a super-slim redesign by the same company that introduced the handheld version last year.

The &quot;Blaze&quot; Sega Mega Drive features a new slim design complete with two control pads and yes - even a cartridge slot.

15 Sega oldies including Sonic &amp; Knuckles, Altered Beast, Golden Axe and Columns come built-in to the console, but the good news is you&#39;ll also be able to stick your old, non-first-party Mega Drive games into the box. It&#39;s multi-region as well.

It sounds like a pretty attractive purchase for Sega fans then. It&#39;s out on April 24 for £39.99, according to Play.&lt;/blockquote&gt;

http://www.play.com/Gadgets/Gadgets/4-/8922102/Sega-Mega-Drive-Console-With-15-Games/Product.html#

Pre ordered! :D Have around 30 mega drive games i&#39;d love to be able to play again on a proper console ;)</description>
    
