              <p><a href="http://www.computerandvideogames.com/article.php?id=210507" class="onebox" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">http://www.computerandvideogames.com/article.php?id=210507</a><br>
[center]<img src="http://medialib.computerandvideogames.com/screens/screenshot_212539_thumb300.jpg" alt width="" height="">[/center]</p>
<blockquote>The Sega Mega Dive is set to return to the shops, courtesy of a super-slim redesign by the same company that introduced the handheld version last year.
<p>The “Blaze” Sega Mega Drive features a new slim design complete with two control pads and yes - even a cartridge slot.</p>
<p>15 Sega oldies including Sonic &amp; Knuckles, Altered Beast, Golden Axe and Columns come built-in to the console, but the good news is you’ll also be able to stick your old, non-first-party Mega Drive games into the box. It’s multi-region as well.</p>
<p>It sounds like a pretty attractive purchase for Sega fans then. It’s out on April 24 for £39.99, according to Play.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><a href="http://www.play.com/Gadgets/Gadgets/4-/8922102/Sega-Mega-Drive-Console-With-15-Games/Product.html#" class="onebox" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">http://www.play.com/Gadgets/Gadgets/4-/8922102/Sega-Mega-Drive-Console-With-15-Games/Product.html#</a></p>
<p>Pre ordered! <img src="https://forum.moparisthebest.com/images/emoji/twitter/smiley.png?v=6" title=":smiley:" class="emoji" alt=":smiley:"> Have around 30 mega drive games i’d love to be able to play again on a proper console <img src="https://forum.moparisthebest.com/images/emoji/twitter/wink.png?v=6" title=":wink:" class="emoji" alt=":wink:"></p>
